# Ello Project
Overview
Ello Project is a full-stack web application built for Ello's frontend challenge. It consists of a frontend client built with React.js and a backend server built with Express.js. The application allows teachers to add and view books. It is a teacher facing UI project.

# Features
A search bar that allows users to search for books by title.
A list of search results that displays the book title, author, and a button to add the book to the students reading list.
A reading list that displays all the books that the teacher has added.
A button to remove a book from the reading list.

# Technologies Used
Frontend:
React.js
Apollo Client for GraphQL requests
MUI and Tailwind CSS for styling
Frontend hosted on Netlify

# Backend:
Node.js
Express.js
GraphQL for API queries and mutations
Backntend hosted on Render


# Getting Started
Prerequisites:
Node.js installed on your machine
NPM or Yarn package manager